      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ECCLESTONE (1) was well fancied when resuming last start and proved too strong, scoring by 2.75 lengths over 1100m at this track. Had switched from Queensland's premier yard and is still shy of his best. Keeps Todd, and he should have these well covered. PREDICTING (2) has been plain his last three but led and went well over this distance prior. The tongue tie comes off, and he's a quinella hope in this line-up. TOUGH IMPACT (5) got closer last time over this trip. Has the rail and 1.5kg claim and can get some of the money. VALKUR (3) is the remaining competitor. Has been struggling to find her best, but goes into the trifecta in a small field.",
